5:
Hello, we're running a special
holiday clinic! Step right up for a
herbal drink to stave off colds!
9:
You drank all the medicine like a big
girl! Here, have a little treat.
12: Yay! Thank you, Miss Santa Lady!
15:
Hehe, that outfit really did the trick.
Plus it's adorable.
19:
It's really for the festival, but I
wanted our patients to experience
at least a little holiday cheer.
23:
But I'm worried it's not appropriate
for a medical facility...
34: You have nothing to worry about.
42:
Medicinal herbs, huh? Sounds like
rubbish to me. Do they even do
anything?
44:
Smells kinda gross too. I'd rather just
drink a Crimson Cow or something.
47:
Um, excuse me! What's a Crimson
Cow? Is it some kind of Shibuyan
medicine?
50:
N-nah, I wouldn't call it medicine. It's
an energy drinkâ€”it perks you right
up. R-right?
52:
Y-yeah! Puts a spring in your step!
But you wouldn't sell something like
that, right? So, uh, bye!
56:
Everyone, I have an announcement:
I want to make one of these "energy
drinks!"
62:
So these energy drinks boost one's
performance?
66:
If those Shibuyan boys are to be
believed, yes. They also sound
somewhat tasty.
70:
I started the recipe by using some of
my healthiest herbs, but
something's still missing.
75:
The drink's supposed to give you
energy, right? How about adding
some of this?
81: Oh, that may work! Let's try!
86:
If you want to prevent fatigue,
nutritional supplements crafted by
alchemists would be a good bet.
94:
And now to add just a few more
herbs to boost potency... This should
work! It has to!
106: H-how did it end up like this?
110:
Teehee, looks like quite the
stimulating concoction.
120:
You sure that's a good idea?! I'm no
expert, but I don't think it's supposed
to GLOW!
125:
It's the only way to verify its efficacy.
An herbalist has a responsibility to
test her creations.
128:
Besides, I can't let all of your help go
to waste!
136:
I'm fine, I'm fine... The taste just
caught me off guard.
141: That's a relief. You had me worried!
146:
Wow, that... wow. It really gets the
blood pumping.
151:
Hehe... hehehe. I feel my power...
surging! I'm filled... with... ENERGY!
155:
I feel like I can do ANYTHING! Like I
can cure any patient!
164:
No, it's not just a feeling. I CAN do
anything! I'll cure EVERYONE!
168:
I can't just sit around here! I've gotta
give this energy drink out to
everyone! I've gotta give out a
MILLION of 'em!
173:
Whoa there, calm down! You sound
like the main character of a
Shibuyan manga or something!
179:
DON'T TRY AND STOP ME! My patients
need me and my medicine!
189:
Form a line, please! There's enough
soup for everyone.
193:
This soup is delicious as always,
Hartlief! It warms you right up!
198:
That's good to hear. I took care to
make sure it goes down easy...
202:
And about that energy drink
situation... I'm really sorry about that!
206:
That concoction was too powerful. I
didn't expect it to have that effect
on me...
211:
No need to apologize. I enjoyed
seeing your passion shine.
215:
It was nice getting a boost from that
energy drink.
218:
But I think a calm demeanor suits
me better when I'm helping others.
221:
That way I can focus on my most
important duty: to heal my patients.
224:
Um, excuse me... Can we have some
of that soup?
231:
Drink up and enjoy the holiday
festival with a warm body and soul!
